description: Number of partitions of n into parts of 21 kinds.
comments: a(n) is the Euler transform of A010860. - _Alois P. Heinz_, Oct 17 2008
links: N. J. A. Sloane, Transforms [From _Alois P. Heinz_, Oct 17 2008]
Index entries for expansions of Product_{k >= 1} (1-x^k)^m
maple: with (numtheory): a:= proc(n) option remember; `if`(n=0, 1, add (add (d*21, d=divisors(j)) *a(n-j), j=1..n)/n) end: seq (a(n), n=0..40); # _Alois P. Heinz_, Oct 17 2008
crossrefs: Cf. 21st column of A144064. - _Alois P. Heinz_, Oct 17 2008
author: _David W. Wilson_, Jun 14 1998
